import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('job').sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='job', y='count', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job types?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['job_count'] = pd.to_numeric(data['job_count'], errors='coerce')
    gender_data = data.groupby(['sex'])['job_count'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    plt.pie(gender_data['job_count'], labels=gender_data['sex'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of job holders?')
    plt.legend(title='Gender', loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
